main event: A circular and bright object was observed orbiting in Baltimore, Maryland on 11 May 1957 for two minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed for two minutes before disappearing, with no reported sound.
It was noted that the cloud cover was 3/10 during the observation.
The object was observed northbound and westbound on Red 17 and Blue 23.
Despite the peculiar flight path, there was insufficient data for evaluation due to the inability to contact the source.
The report includes photographs of the observed object.
